Base:Descriptions.Base:Description: tiny mouse
A tiny mouse with russet orange fur, white underparts, pink nose and paws, whiskers, beady black eyes, small ears and a long, naked prehensile tail.
A tiny mouse with russet orange fur, white underparts and a long, naked tail.
back
The back of a mouse covered with thick russet orange fur.
The russet orange furred back of a mouse.
belly
The quivering belly of a mouse covered in whitish fur.
The belly of a mouse covered in whitish fur.
cheek
The russet orange fur covered cheek of a mouse, capable of storing grain or other food to take back to it's nest.
The russet orange fur covered cheek of a mouse.
breast
The tiny breast of a mouse, covered in soft whitish fur.
The breast of a mouse, covered in whitish fur.
ear
The small and hairy ear of a mouse; pink skinned on the inside and covered in russet orange fur on the back. The ear twitches alertly, detecting the slightest sound.
A small russet orange furred mouse ear.
eye
The beady black eye of a mouse.
The black eye of a mouse.
pair of eyes
A pair of beady black mouse eyes.
A pair of black mouse eyes.
paw
The tiny pink-skinned paw of a mouse, with long toes and claws that enable it to easily grasp and climb grass stalks and other plants.
The tiny pink paw of a mouse.
head

The russet orange fur covered head of a mouse, with small ears set towards the back, beady black eyes, blunt pink nose, cheeks capable of storing grain or other food for transport, a white furred chin, twitching whiskers, and a mouth with teeth suitable for gnawing plants.
The russet orange fur covered head of a mouse, with small ears, black eyes, pink nose, whiskers, and mouth.
mouse breast
By observing the mouse's breast carefully you detect a rapidly beating heart.
The whitish, furry breast of a mouse.
leg
The nimble leg of a mouse covered with russet orange fur on the outer side and whitish fur on the inner side.
The leg of a mouse covered with russet orange fur on the outer side and whitish fur on the inner side.
muzzle
The russet orange furred muzzle of a mouse, with a blunt pink nose, luxuriant whiskers, white furred chin and a mouth equipped with teeth suitable for gnawing plants.
The russet orange furred muzzle of a mouse, with a pink nose, whiskers and mouth.
neck
The short neck of a mouse covered in russet orange fur.
The short furry neck of a mouse.
side
The sides of a mouse, covered with russet orange fur.
The furry sides of a mouse.
mouse tail
The naked, prehensile tail of a mouse; almost as long as it's body, the tail can wrap around plant stalks to help the mouse steady it's self or quickly move from plant to plant.
The long, naked tail of a mouse.
teeth
The yellowish teeth of a mouse; long front incisors help the mouse harvest plants.
The yellowish teeth of a mouse.
